<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-320-032  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 320 032.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  April 9 1990 n462 p3(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Network managers look for support: claim suppliers stress salesover user needs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Duffy, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A small association of network managers, dubbed the Council forNetwork Managers, has convened to discuss common problemsassociated with their relations with systems vendors andintegrators.andP;  One of the main complaints heard at the meeting wasthat vendors are not responsive to users service and supportrequirements.andP;  Users say service and support is inadequate when itis offered and is usually accompanied by solutions that involvepurchasing more hardware and software.andP;  Users warn they will soonlook elsewhere for solutions if suppliers cannot provide costeffective ways of keeping networks running at peak efficiency without costly patchwork remedies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksNetwork ManagementVendor RelationsEnd UsersCustom SystemsCustomer RelationsComputer Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>